olive oil
1 tomato
½ lemon
1 mint
1 carrot
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
½ packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
2 tbs water
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
½ packet soy sauce mix
1 packet Crushed Peanuts

• Slice tomato and lemon into wedges. Pick and thinly slice mint leaves. Using a vegetable peeler, peel carrot into ribbons.
• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning and the plain flour. Add beef and toss to combine.
• In a small bowl, combine sweet chilli sauce, ginger & lemongrass paste (see ingredients), a good squeeze of lemon juice and the water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips, tossing, in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat and add sweet chilli mixture, tossing beef to coat.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• In a large bowl, combine tomato, carrot, mint, shredded cabbage mix, baby kale, soy sauce mix (see ingredients) and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with pepper.

• Divide mint salad between bowls.
• Top with Vietnamese-style beef.
• Garnish with crushed peanuts. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!